[SN]TITLE[SN]
Newport Gwent Dragons: Adam Warren signs new Dragons contract

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Adam Warren has become the seventh Newport Gwent Dragons player to commit his future to the Welsh region.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Warren, 25, joined Lewis Evans, Hallam Amos, Brok Harris, Nic Cudd, Rynard Landman and Ed Jackson in signing a new Dragons deal.
The centre or wing won a Test cap against the Barbarians in 2012 and has also played for Wales Under-20s and the Sevens side.
Warren joined the Dragons from the Scarlets in 2015.
